          </svg>
        </div>
        <figcaption>
          <span class="fig">fig. 01</span>
          <span class="cap">A single Beckn transaction crosses four boundaries — two private, two public — and ONIX is the translator at each network edge.</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p>
        Each ONIX node speaks two languages. To the backend it speaks HTTP-and-JSON
        in whatever shape the operator prefers. To the network it speaks the
        Beckn v2.0 protocol — strictly signed, strictly typed, strictly versioned.
        Everything in this document is about <span class="ital">how it negotiates between those two sides</span>.
      </p>

    </div>
